headline: Taking Feminism to Heart, if Not to the Caucuses
abstract: In the Trump era, some voters say the power of a symbolic first is overshadowed by anxiety about defeating him.
lead_paragraph: WINTERSET, Iowa — Almost exactly three years ago, Leila Schlenker marveled at the crowds at the Women’s March in Des Moines, which drew more than 26,000 people to the grounds of the state capitol and reminded her of the large social protests of the 1960s.
